Spatz -<br>
Just wondering -<br>
Why do you assume Andy is drunk or ? just because his message got garbled?<br>
Why do you persist in posting vitriolic b.s. at a site erected to commemorate one of the greatest attempts to bring about reconciliation (I refer to Maya Lin's design, which is , after all, the reason this web site exists)?<br>
It's definitely a good thing you got out of the shrink business, because you've got a lot of stuff to work out yourself.<br>
The war was wrong - how many times do you want to hear veterans say it?  But it was, as old Ronnie Reagan said (God, I hate to admit that man was right), a noble attempt.  As Andy has pointed out, both in word and deed, many of us who were there, were there out of a genuine desire to serve our fellow humans.  Many protestors were where they were out of a genuine desire to serve, as well.  We have at least some common ground.  Can't we build on that?  Or do we have to continue the War to our graves?
